<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 4:10PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm in northeastern Macomb and northern St.
Clair Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Memphis, or near Richmond, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds around 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could damage unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Memphis around 420 PM EDT.
Emmett around 440 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include North Street, Adair,
Rattle Run, Goodells, Brockway, Smiths Creek, Wadhams, Riley Center,
Fort Gratiot and Avoca.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
